title: The Adventures of Tom Sawyer
description: Mark Twain, 1876

#tom: blue
#huck: green
#becky: pink
#injunJoe: red
#aunt: orange

section Early Mischief
1876-06-01/1876-06-03: Tom tricks boys into whitewashing the fence #tom
He convinces them it's a privilege, collects treasures in trade.

1876-06-04: Tom meets Becky Thatcher at school #tom #becky
Falls in love at first sight. Shows off in the schoolyard.

1876-06-05/1876-06-06: Tom and Huck find a dead cat #tom #huck
They plan to visit the graveyard at midnight to cure warts.

section The Murder
1876-06-07: Midnight at the graveyard #tom #huck #injunJoe
Tom and Huck witness Injun Joe murder Dr. Robinson. They swear a blood oath to keep silent.

1876-06-08/1876-06-14: Tom and Huck live in fear #tom #huck
Muff Potter is blamed for the murder. The boys are tormented by guilt.

section Running Away
1876-06-15/1876-06-20: Tom, Huck and Joe Harper run away to Jackson's Island #tom #huck
They play pirates on the island. The town believes they drowned.

1876-06-21: The boys return for their own funeral #tom #huck
They appear in the church during the memorial service. The whole town rejoices.

section The Trial
1876-07-01/1876-07-03: Muff Potter's murder trial #tom #injunJoe
Tom breaks his oath and testifies against Injun Joe. Joe escapes through the courtroom window.

section The Cave
1876-07-10/1876-07-13: Tom and Becky lost in McDougal's Cave #tom #becky #injunJoe
They wander for days in the dark. Tom discovers Injun Joe is hiding in the cave.

1876-07-14: Tom finds the way out #tom #becky
He follows a distant speck of daylight and leads Becky to safety.

1876-07-20: Injun Joe found dead in the sealed cave #injunJoe
Judge Thatcher had the cave entrance sealed. Joe starved behind the iron door.

section The Treasure
1876-07-25: Tom and Huck find Injun Joe's treasure #tom #huck
Twelve thousand dollars in gold coins hidden in the cave. They are rich.

1876-07-26/1876-07-30: The boys become famous #tom #huck
The Widow Douglas adopts Huck. Tom and Huck plan new adventures.
